<font color="#FF0000">BROTHERS OF CHOICE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 18:13:03 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Our God and the soldier we alike adore<br>
Even at the brink of danger, not before:<br>
After deliverance, both alike requited,<br>
God is forgotten, and the soldier slighted.<br><br>
    Francis Quarles:  Emblems, 1635<br><br>
On becoming soldiers we have not ceased<br>
to be citizens.<br><br>
It has all happened before.  The first of several<br>
quotes.
